The paper deals with video foreground-background separation, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The use of optical flow and compressive measurements suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). The incorporation of prior information and the use of online methods suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the use of multiple prior information suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
